environmental.systemBoundary: The system boundaries comprise the cradle-to-gate process for manufacturing double pane IGUs. The manufacturing energy for assembly of the double pane IGU was assumed to be 15 kWh/sqm of window unit (Athena 1999). Upstream data includes glass pane manufacture, energy production, chemicals production, aluminium production, and transportation of raw materials to manufacturing facility. Packaging is excluded.

name: Double Pane IGU
description: Insulated glass units (IGUs) designed for commercial applications can be made with a variety of glass types, specialty coatings, and spacer materials.  This CP describes a standard IGU made with two panes of uncoated, clear, flat glass, an aluminum spacer filled with a molecular sieve desiccant, and assembled with a primary seal of polyisobutylene and secondary seal of silicone.  The space between the panes of glass is filled with air only. This CP does not include any framing materials, or products required for installation.   Calculations are based on a 1 inch thick 14x14 inch IGU.
